8:
Huh? What do you mean the quest 
isn't available anymore?
10:
Sorry, bud. Especially since you came 
all the way out here, but yeah... that 
one's already been done.
11:
I guess headquarters didn't get the 
memo in time. Whoops.
16:
Well, if you're available... how about 
this quest? Mrs. Chesney next door 
needs somebody to fix her leaky roof.
19: Do I look like a carpenter to you?!
25:
Can'tcha see I'm tryna get some shut-
eye here? My head's killin' me.
28:
You should be thankful I'm even letting 
you stay here, you drunkard! This isn't 
an inn!
31:
Hmph... Is that any way to talk to one 
of your best patrons?
34:
Sorry. He ain't a bad guy—er, well he 
isn't an upstanding citizen or anything 
like that either. What I'm trying to say 
is, feel free to ignore him.
41: I can still hear you, ya know!
43:
He's actually the one that took care of 
the quest you originally came here for.
46:
By himself? That was supposed to be 
a three-person job, wasn't it?
50:
Three-person job to take out some 
small fry? Hah! The guild's gone soft... 
I barely even broke a sweat.
53:
But don't expect me to share any of 
the profit—already spent it all on 
booze!
66:
Heh... Good one, missy. You must be in 
dire straits if you're tryin' to get 
someone like me to join your party.
68:
Too bad, 'cause I'm not about that life 
anymore. I've left that all behind, see—
78:
Those bastards... Indiscriminately 
shooting just to get me now?
82: Whoa. How did you know they were—
90: Wh-what the hell just happened here?!
93: Sorry, but could you clean this up?
95: They ain't dead. So be careful.
100: W-wait, I can't take all this!
103:
Throwing daggers, crossbows, and 
broadswords... Yeesh. He took 'em all 
out on his own like it was nothing too.
107: Stella? W-wait, where are you going?
120:
I already told you, didn't I? I'm not 
about the adventurer life anymore, so 
run home.
123:
Your eyes. They remind me of 
someone I know.
128: Where do you plan on going?
139:
So you wanna know where I'm going? 
Sure, I'll tell ya. I'm on the run.
143: Always have been, and always will be.
144: Ain't nobody catchin' me... not yet.
148: In that case, I have a proposal.
154:
If you don't wish to be found, I know 
the perfect place.
161:
Hahahah! You weren't kidding!
Multiple worlds? I must be dreamin'...
162:
I heard the rumors here and there in 
the Kaleidoscope, but who would've 
guessed it'd be in a place like this!
170:
Did you bring another person back 
with you?
*sigh* Well... At least Alk's with you this 
time, so I suppose it should be fine.
178:
Not bad, not bad... Yeah. I could see 
myself stayin' in a place like this.
180:
But let's make this clear—I've long 
retired from adventurer life, so don't 
expect me to act like one.
185:
Of course. Please make yourself at 
home.
